\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 Heat the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/grill/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 grill}} to high.\
Lightly brush the watermelon slices with vegetable oil and season with salt. Arrange on the grill and grill until you have visible grill marks on both sides. Remove the rind and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/chop/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 chop}} the flesh into large chunks. Add the watermelon flesh to a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/blender/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 blender}}, along with 1 cup of water and blend until liquefied. Strain the juice, through a fine {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/strainer/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 strainer}}, into a bowl. Discard the pulp and reserve watermelon juice.\
In a large bowl or glass pitcher, combine the tequila, simple syrup, lime juice and watermelon {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/schnapps/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 schnapps}}. Add the grilled watermelon juice, and stir. Pour into serving glasses and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/garnish/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 garnish}} with reserved slices of grilled watermelon and a jalapeno pepper.\
Jalapeno Infused Simple Syrup:\
